Self-proclaimed Prophet Shepherd Bushiri and his wife, Mary appear at the Pretoria Magistrate Court. JOHANNESBURG - Self-proclaimed Prophet, Shepherd Bushiri and his wife Mary, are expected to find out if they will be released on bail. READ: Bushiri couple to remain in custody until Monday Bushiri handed himself over to the police on Tuesday, while his wife, Mary, was arrested. They are facing charges of fraud, theft, and money laundering to the value of over R100-million. READ: Bushiri's SA permanent residency in question The State which is opposing bail says it needs more time to investigate but, the Bushiris contend they can not be held while investigations continue.